<title>MEXICO: FOREIGN INVESTMENT IN MEXICO SECURITIES UP IN JULY.</title>
<headline>FOREIGN INVESTMENT IN MEXICO SECURITIES UP IN JULY.</headline>
<dateline>MEXICO CITY 1997-08-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>Foreign investment in Mexican securities rose 15.64 percent at the end of July to $53.39 billion from $46.17 billion on June 30, the Mexican Stock Exchange said on Monday.</p>
<p>It said foreign investment in stocks rose 15.88 percent to $49.65 billion, while in the money market it rose 12.51 percent to $3.75 billion from the month before.  </p>
